-- Ferragamo Gains Most Since July as CEO Positive on 2013 Outlook
-- B y   A n d r e w   R o b e r t s   a n d   P a u l   J a r v i s
-- 2013-01-14T10:03:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-14/ferragamo-gains-most-since-july-as-ceo-positive-on-2013-outlook.html
Salvatore Ferragamo SpA, (SFER)  an Italian
maker of luxury sandals, rose the most in six months in Milan
trading after Chief Executive Officer Michele Norsa gave an
upbeat appraisal of the fourth quarter and outlook for 2013.  The  shares  gained as much as 5.9 percent to 18.83 euros,
the highest intraday price since April 30 and biggest percentage
advance since July 13.  The fourth quarter showed a “positive trend” with
“significant” growth worldwide during December, Norsa said in
an interview before the company’s fashion show in Milan
yesterday. The CEO also said he sees a “positive” 2013, helped
by demand from Chinese and Latin America shoppers.  The Florence, Italy-based company plans to develop a U.S.
store network this year, according to Norsa.  Ferragamo was up 5.6 percent at 18.78 euros as of 10:48
a.m. in Milan, valuing the company at 3.2 billion euros ($4.3
billion).  To contact the reporters on this story:
